(129, 'student', '1st', '', 'DeepDetect: DeepFaked Media Detector', 'The rapid advancement of artificial intelligence has led to the creation of highly realistic synthetic media, commonly known as deepfakes. These manipulated videos, images, and audio clips pose serious threats to digital integrity, misinformation control, and public trust. DeepDetect is an AI-driven system designed to accurately identify and flag deepfaked media using advanced deep learning models such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). The system analyzes facial inconsistencies, pixel-level artifacts, and temporal irregularities to distinguish between genuine and altered content. Through extensive testing and dataset training, DeepDetect demonstrates high accuracy and reliability in detecting deepfakes, offering a scalable solution for media verification in journalism, social media platforms, and cybersecurity contexts.', 'DeepDetect provides a critical defense mechanism against the growing challenge of deepfake technology. By leveraging deep learning and image analysis, the system enhances digital security and promotes authenticity in online media. Its application can help prevent the spread of misinformation, protect individuals from identity manipulation, and support ethical AI use across digital ecosystems. Future improvements may include integrating real-time detection capabilities and cross-platform compatibility to strengthen trust in digital communication. Ultimately, DeepDetect contributes to building a safer, more transparent information environment.', 'Joevelyn Fajardo', '[\"Solis, Jhon Rogelio\",\"Pago, Jhondhel \",\"Murillo, Ken Jairu\",\"Agang, James Chadwick\"]', 2, 23, '9', '\"Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure\"', '{\"0\":0.03053794801235199,\"1\":0.003159541403874755,\"2\":0.027053318917751312,\"3\":0.055298373103141785,\"4\":0.0012176379095762968,\"5\":0.0025479921605437994,\"6\":0.003092249156907201,\"7\":0.05944639444351196,\"8\":0.6022366881370544,\"9\":0.05356534197926521,\"10\":0.009742380119860172,\"11\":0.0020803543739020824,\"12\":0.0022458091843873262,\"13\":0.001409657415933907,\"14\":0.002335701836273074,\"15\":0.12561587989330292,\"16\":0.018414676189422607}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 04:55:02', 44, 2023),
(130, 'student', '1st', '', 'Assessing Emotional State in EARIST Students through Machine Learning Analysis of Vocal Tone During Pocket Book Reading ', 'The emotional well-being of students plays a crucial role in their academic performance and overall mental health. This study, “Assessing Emotional State in EARIST Students through Machine Learning Analysis of Vocal Tone During Pocket Book Reading,” explores how voice-based emotion recognition can provide insights into students’ emotional states. Using machine learning models such as Support Vector Machines (SVM) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), the system analyzes vocal tone, pitch, frequency, and intensity during pocket book reading sessions. The goal is to detect emotional indicators such as happiness, sadness, stress, or calmness. Data were collected from recorded voice samples of EARIST students and processed through audio feature extraction techniques like MFCC (Mel Frequency Cepstral Coefficients). The results demonstrate that machine learning can effectively classify emotional states with promising accuracy, offering a new perspective on emotional assessment in educational settings.', 'The findings of this study show that vocal tone analysis using machine learning can serve as a reliable and non-intrusive method for assessing students’ emotional well-being. By identifying emotional patterns through speech, educators and counselors can better understand students’ mental and emotional conditions, leading to improved support systems and learning environments. This approach not only enhances emotional awareness but also promotes mental health monitoring using innovative technology. Future studies may include real-time emotion tracking and multimodal data integration, such as facial expressions and physiological signals, to improve accuracy and applicability in educational psychology.', 'Arjo Ladia', '[\"Vinas, Rafael \",\"Durante, Jude Michael \",\"Abalos, Rochelle \",\"Pil, Marck Darrel\"]', 2, 23, '[3]', '[\"Good Health and Well-being\"]', '{\"0\":0,\"1\":0,\"2\":1,\"3\":0,\"4\":0,\"5\":0,\"6\":0,\"7\":0,\"8\":0,\"9\":0,\"10\":0,\"11\":0,\"12\":0,\"13\":0,\"14\":0,\"15\":0,\"16\":0}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 04:57:04', 44, 2023),
(131, 'student', '1st', '', 'Detecting Malicious Advertisements Through Text and Image: A Fusion Approach Using Naïve Bayes and CNN Algorithms', 'The increasing prevalence of malicious online advertisements poses significant threats to user privacy, cybersecurity, and digital trust. This study, “Detecting Malicious Advertisements Through Text and Image: A Fusion Approach Using Naïve Bayes and CNN Algorithms,” proposes a hybrid detection system that integrates both textual and visual analysis for improved accuracy. The textual content of advertisements is processed and classified using the Naïve Bayes algorithm to identify suspicious keywords and linguistic patterns, while the image components are analyzed through a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to detect deceptive or inappropriate visual elements. By fusing the results of both models, the system achieves a higher precision rate in identifying malicious ads compared to single-modality methods. Experimental evaluations demonstrate that the fusion approach enhances detection reliability, helping users and organizations filter harmful online content effectively.', 'The fusion of text-based and image-based analysis provides a robust solution for detecting malicious advertisements. By combining the strengths of Naïve Bayes in text classification and CNN in image recognition, the system successfully identifies potential threats that might bypass traditional detection methods. This research contributes to enhancing online safety, protecting users from phishing, scams, and malware embedded in digital advertisements. Future work may involve real-time ad monitoring, integration with web browsers, and expansion to multilingual datasets for broader applicability. Overall, this study underscores the importance of intelligent, AI-driven systems in promoting a safer digital ecosystem.', 'Jefferson A. Costales', '[\"Malabanan, Hazel Joy M.\",\"Guevarra, Icecube Williams \",\"Bautista, Jehu Hallel F.\",\"Base, Owen L.\",\"Asim, John Paulo F. \"]', 2, 23, '9', '\"Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure\"', '{\"0\":0.01913061924278736,\"1\":0.00617157481610775,\"2\":0.1443723887205124,\"3\":0.0024099552538245916,\"4\":0.00045766576658934355,\"5\":0.00319093419238925,\"6\":0.004991582129150629,\"7\":0.04197823256254196,\"8\":0.28761646151542664,\"9\":0.07653430849313736,\"10\":0.005175047554075718,\"11\":0.002354256808757782,\"12\":0.002738481154665351,\"13\":0.0008244460332207382,\"14\":0.0025340993888676167,\"15\":0.28728339076042175,\"16\":0.11223661154508591}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 04:59:11', 44, 2023),
(132, 'student', '1st', '', 'QLBase: Decentralizable backend solution alternative to traditional noSQL and cloudbased services using ACID and LZW Algorithm', 'The growing reliance on centralized cloud-based and NoSQL databases raises concerns about data privacy, scalability, and system dependency on third-party providers. QLBase proposes a decentralizable backend solution designed to address these limitations by integrating ACID-compliant transaction management with LZW (Lempel–Ziv–Welch) compression for optimized data storage and transmission. The system enables distributed nodes to store and process data securely while maintaining consistency, reliability, and performance comparable to conventional centralized databases. By implementing a hybrid data structure and efficient compression scheme, QLBase minimizes latency and bandwidth usage, providing a lightweight yet robust backend alternative. Experimental evaluations demonstrate that QLBase offers improved fault tolerance, reduced operational cost, and enhanced control over data ownership—key factors for modern decentralized application (dApp) architectures.', 'QLBase presents an innovative step toward decentralizing backend systems while maintaining the stability and reliability of traditional database models. Through the use of ACID principles, it ensures data integrity and transaction safety, while LZW compression enhances efficiency and resource utilization. The proposed system promotes user autonomy, resilience, and transparency in data management, addressing critical challenges in centralized infrastructures. Future work may explore blockchain integration, multi-node synchronization optimization, and cross-platform deployment to strengthen its applicability for large-scale decentralized ecosystems. Ultimately, QLBase contributes to advancing open, secure, and efficient digital infrastructure for next-generation applications.', 'Jefferson A. Costales', '[\"Reyes, Wilhem John Damiel\",\"Duran, Emmanuel\",\"Baldivicio, Jonathan\",\"Baldivicio, Jonathan\"]', 2, 23, '9', '\"Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure\"', '{\"0\":0.004822199232876301,\"1\":0.0016452206764370203,\"2\":0.05501183494925499,\"3\":0.00241592968814075,\"4\":0.00020955907530151308,\"5\":0.000781714916229248,\"6\":0.0013318981509655714,\"7\":0.04759454354643822,\"8\":0.8663831949234009,\"9\":0.0020531006157398224,\"10\":0.002868905197829008,\"11\":0.0005061856936663389,\"12\":0.0009037178824655712,\"13\":0.000389774824725464,\"14\":0.0014756469754502177,\"15\":0.00784758385270834,\"16\":0.003759004408493638}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 05:02:22', 44, 2023),
(133, 'student', '1st', '', 'ResearchKoTo: A WebBased AI - Driven Contextual Analysis of Scientific Articles for Review of Related Studies', 'Conducting a Review of Related Studies (RRS) is a critical yet time-consuming step in academic research, often requiring extensive reading and analysis of numerous scientific articles. ResearchKoTo is a web-based, AI-driven system designed to streamline this process by automatically performing contextual analysis of research papers. Using Natural Language Processing (NLP) and machine learning algorithms, the system identifies key themes, summarizes related literature, and classifies studies based on research domains and methodologies. By processing abstracts and full-text content, ResearchKoTo helps users extract relevant information more efficiently, reducing manual workload and improving the accuracy of literature synthesis. The platform provides an intelligent, user-friendly interface accessible to students, educators, and researchers, supporting data-driven and well-informed academic writing.', 'ResearchKoTo demonstrates the potential of artificial intelligence in transforming academic research workflows. By leveraging contextual analysis through NLP, the system enhances the process of reviewing related studies, making it faster, more consistent, and less prone to human error. This innovation not only improves research efficiency but also encourages academic integrity and accessibility to scientific knowledge. Future developments may include integrating citation analysis, semantic search, and multilingual support to further expand its usability. Ultimately, ResearchKoTo contributes to the modernization of research methodologies and the promotion of intelligent academic tools for the digital era.', 'Jefferson A. Costales', '[\"Honey Dee T.\",\"King Shane B. Esler\",\"Cristian C. Gabarda\",\"Lorena Justine Rei H. Mallen\"]', 2, 23, '[4]', '[\"Quality Education\"]', '{\"0\":0,\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":1,\"4\":0,\"5\":0,\"6\":0,\"7\":0,\"8\":0,\"9\":0,\"10\":0,\"11\":0,\"12\":0,\"13\":0,\"14\":0,\"15\":0,\"16\":0}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 05:04:38', 44, 2023),
(134, 'student', '1st', '', 'An Advanced Integrated IntranetBased Simulation System for the College of Hospitality and Tourism Management of EARIST Manila', 'The College of Hospitality and Tourism Management (CHTM) of EARIST Manila requires a modern and efficient system to enhance academic training and administrative operations. This study, “An Advanced Integrated Intranet-Based Simulation System,” aims to develop a comprehensive platform designed to simulate real-world hospitality and tourism management processes within a controlled digital environment. The system integrates modules for hotel and restaurant operations, reservation management, event planning, and performance assessment, all accessible through the institution’s intranet. By providing an interactive, hands-on learning experience, the platform bridges the gap between theoretical instruction and practical application. It also supports faculty in monitoring student activities and generating analytical reports for academic evaluation. The implementation of this intranet-based simulation system demonstrates the potential of technology-driven education in improving learning engagement, operational efficiency, and institutional innovation.', 'The development of the Advanced Integrated Intranet-Based Simulation System significantly enhances the teaching and learning experience within the College of Hospitality and Tourism Management. By providing a centralized and interactive platform, the system allows students to gain practical experience in a simulated professional environment while enabling instructors to manage, assess, and guide learners more effectively. This innovation not only improves educational outcomes but also strengthens institutional efficiency and digital transformation within EARIST Manila. Future improvements may include expanding system functionality to cover industry partnerships, online certifications, and real-time analytics. Overall, the project contributes to advancing education and preparing students for real-world challenges in the hospitality and tourism sector.', 'Jefferson A. Costales', '[\"Veloso, Audjan Neil\",\"Diaz, France Yuan\",\"Decena, Ian Joseph\",\"Concon, Christian James\"]', 2, 23, '[4]', '[\"Quality Education\"]', '{\"0\":0,\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":1,\"4\":0,\"5\":0,\"6\":0,\"7\":0,\"8\":0,\"9\":0,\"10\":0,\"11\":0,\"12\":0,\"13\":0,\"14\":0,\"15\":0,\"16\":0}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 05:11:25', 44, 2023),
(135, 'student', '1st', '', 'Detection of Abnormal Heartbeat using Audio Spectrogram and Hybrid CNN-LSTM Model ', 'Cardiovascular diseases remain one of the leading causes of mortality worldwide, making early and accurate detection of abnormal heartbeats crucial. This study, “Detection of Abnormal Heartbeat Using Audio Spectrogram and Hybrid CNN-LSTM Model,” proposes an AI-driven approach for classifying heart sound signals. Heartbeat audio recordings are converted into spectrograms, capturing both temporal and frequency information, which are then analyzed using a hybrid Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) model. The CNN component extracts spatial features from the spectrograms, while the LSTM captures temporal dependencies in the heartbeat patterns. Experimental results demonstrate that the hybrid model achieves high accuracy in distinguishing between normal and abnormal heart sounds, providing a reliable, non-invasive diagnostic tool for cardiovascular health monitoring.', 'The hybrid CNN-LSTM model effectively detects abnormal heartbeats from audio spectrograms, combining spatial and temporal feature extraction for enhanced classification performance. This approach provides a promising, non-invasive method for early cardiovascular risk assessment, supporting timely medical intervention and continuous patient monitoring. Future enhancements may include real-time detection, integration with wearable devices, and deployment in telemedicine platforms to broaden accessibility. Overall, this system contributes to improving healthcare outcomes and promoting proactive management of heart-related conditions.', 'James Darryl D. Bungay', '[\"Bernal, Kyla Marie\",\"Quilatan, Denzel\",\"Paderog, John Gabriel\",\"Fabregas, Mick Angelo\"]', 2, 23, '3', '\"Good Health and Well-being\"', '{\"0\":0.000017367468899465166,\"1\":0.0001326665806118399,\"2\":0.9987743496894836,\"3\":0.000052533814596245065,\"4\":0.000002032798420259496,\"5\":0.00001484