(136, 'student', '1st', '', 'Predictive Modelling for Effective Study Time and Distraction Identification using Machine Learning', 'Effective study habits are critical for academic success, yet students often struggle with time management and distractions. This study, “Predictive Modelling for Effective Study Time and Distraction Identification Using Machine Learning,” proposes a data-driven approach to monitor and optimize students’ study patterns. By collecting behavioral and environmental data, including study duration, device usage, and engagement metrics, the system employs machine learning algorithms such as Random Forests, Support Vector Machines (SVM), and Gradient Boosting to predict optimal study times and detect periods of distraction. The predictive model provides actionable insights and personalized recommendations to enhance focus, productivity, and learning efficiency. Experimental evaluations indicate that the system accurately identifies distractions and suggests strategies for effective study planning, empowering students to improve academic performance.', 'The predictive modelling framework successfully identifies distractions and recommends effective study periods using machine learning techniques. By offering personalized insights into study behavior, the system helps students manage time efficiently, reduce distractions, and enhance overall learning outcomes. Future improvements could include real-time monitoring, integration with mobile and web applications, and adaptive feedback based on user progress. Overall, this approach demonstrates the potential of AI-driven tools to support academic success and foster better study habits among students.', 'James Darryl D. Bungay', '[\"Cabe, Ar-Jay\",\"Arcayan, MheAnne \",\"Tupas, Miguel G. \",\"Abad, Jhey Marc\"]', 2, 23, '[4]', '[\"Quality Education\"]', '{\"0\":0,\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":1,\"4\":0,\"5\":0,\"6\":0,\"7\":0,\"8\":0,\"9\":0,\"10\":0,\"11\":0,\"12\":0,\"13\":0,\"14\":0,\"15\":0,\"16\":0}', '