(137, 'student', '1st', '', 'Transforming Distance Learning: Developing a Virtual Reality Application for Remote Education', 'The shift to remote education has highlighted the limitations of traditional online learning platforms, particularly in engagement and interactivity. This study, “Transforming Distance Learning: Developing a Virtual Reality (VR) Application for Remote Education,” presents a VR-based learning environment designed to enhance student engagement, collaboration, and comprehension. The application creates immersive simulations of classrooms, laboratories, and interactive educational scenarios, allowing students to experience realistic learning experiences from remote locations. Key features include real-time interaction, 3D visualization of concepts, and gamified learning activities. Initial user testing demonstrates increased engagement, improved understanding of complex topics, and higher motivation among students compared to conventional online learning methods.', 'The development of a Virtual Reality application for remote education offers a transformative approach to distance learning by providing immersive, interactive, and engaging educational experiences. By bridging the gap between physical and virtual classrooms, the system enhances comprehension, retention, and collaboration among learners. Future developments may include integration with learning management systems, adaptive learning paths, and multi-user collaborative environments. Overall, this VR application contributes to improving access to quality education and fostering innovative teaching and learning methodologies.', 'Melody Gabas ', '[\"Rojo\",\"Ramos\",\"Capisonda\",\"Ignacio\"]', 2, 23, '4', '\"Quality Education\"', '{\"0\":0.0044892155565321445,\"1\":0.009793175384402275,\"2\":0.00187194743193686,\"3\":0.7619031071662903,\"4\":0.0010432697599753737,\"5\":0.0008062405395321548,\"6\":0.0005212201504036784,\"7\":0.003219920676201582,\"8\":0.19659142196178436,\"9\":0.0020123077