(140, 'student', '1st', '', 'SafelyEqualizeIT: Facilitating Safe Transitioning for LGBTQIA+ Individuals through Web-based Consultation System for TransHealth PH', 'LGBTQIA+ individuals seeking gender-affirming healthcare often face barriers such as limited access to professional guidance, social stigma, and fragmented medical information. SafelyEqualizeIT addresses these challenges by providing a web-based consultation system designed to facilitate safe and informed transitioning for transgender individuals in the Philippines. The platform enables users to connect with certified healthcare providers, access educational resources, and receive personalized guidance on medical, psychological, and legal aspects of gender transition. Through secure communication channels and an intuitive interface, the system ensures confidentiality and accessibility. Preliminary user testing indicates improved knowledge, confidence, and access to professional support among the target community.', 'SafelyEqualizeIT demonstrates a practical solution for supporting transgender individuals in navigating the complex process of gender transitioning safely and responsibly. By integrating web-based consultations with educational resources and professional guidance, the platform enhances accessibility, reduces risks associated with uninformed decisions, and promotes overall well-being. Future enhancements may include multilingual support, mobile application integration, and AI-driven resource recommendations. Overall, this project contributes to health equity, social inclusion, and empowerment of LGBTQIA+ individuals seeking gender-affirming care.', 'Arlene Evangelista', '[\"Porcal, Mary Grace\",\"Lacambra, Jas\",\"Cillo, Nicole\",\"Constantino, Roniel\"]', 2, 23, '[5]', '[\"Gender Equality\"]', '{\"0\":0,\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":0,\"4\":1,\"5\":0,\"6\":0,\"7\":0,\"8\":0,\"9\":0,\"10\":0,\"11\":0,\"12\":0,\"13\":0,\"14\":0,\"15\":0,\"16\":0}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 05:20:59', 44, 2023),
(141, 'student', '1st', '', 'EARIST SmartHandbook: An Android Student Handbook Application with Query bot for Student Assistance', 'Navigating academic life can be challenging for students without easy access to essential information and assistance. EARIST SmartHandbook is an Android-based student handbook application designed to centralize important institutional information and provide instant support through a query bot. The application allows students to access schedules, announcements, policies, campus facilities, and other academic resources conveniently on their mobile devices. The integrated query bot utilizes AI to answer student inquiries in real-time, reducing delays in obtaining information and enhancing overall campus engagement. User testing indicates increased accessibility, improved response efficiency, and greater student satisfaction.', 'EARIST SmartHandbook provides a comprehensive solution to streamline student access to institutional information and assistance. By combining an intuitive Android interface with an AI-powered query bot, the application improves efficiency, supports academic planning, and enhances the overall student experience. Future developments may include personalized notifications, integration with learning management systems, and multilingual support to broaden accessibility. Overall, the project demonstrates the potential of mobile applications in improving student services, engagement, and academic success.', 'Edgardo Sison', '[\"Unlayao, Rannilyn\",\"Traballo, Jeffrey\",\"Oduya, Marc Louise\",\"Castroverde, Kim Francis\",\"Urgelles, Maria Jannah\"]', 2, 23, '[4]', '[\"Quality Education\"]', '{\"0\":0,\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":1,\"4\":0,\"5\":0,\"6\":0,\"7\":0,\"8\":0,\"9\":0,\"10\":0,\"11\":0,\"12\":0,\"13\":0,\"14\":0,\"15\":0,\"16\":0}', 'completed', '2025-11-11 05:23:02', 44, 2023),
(142, 'student', '1st', '', 'SnapShop: A WebBased IGP Shop for EARIST Merchandise, Books, and Uniforms', 'Accessing official merchandise, books, and uniforms can be challenging for students and faculty, often requiring physical visits to campus stores. SnapShop is a web-based IGP shop designed to streamline the purchase of EARIST merchandise, academic books, and uniforms through an online platform. The system features an intuitive interface for browsing, selecting, and securely purchasing items, with options for payment and delivery tracking. By digitizing the campus retail experience, SnapShop improves accessibility, reduces queue times, and ensures convenience for the university community. Initial testing demonstrates high usability, faster transaction processing, and increased satisfaction among users.', 'SnapShop provides a practical solution for modernizing campus retail operations, offering students and staff an efficient, accessible, and secure way to purchase merchandise, books, and uniforms. The platform enhances user experience, streamlines administrative processes, and supports campus operations by reducing in-person workload. Future improvements may include mobile app integration, inventory management optimization, and personalized recommendations for users. Overall, SnapShop contributes to the digital transformation of campus services, promoting convenience, efficiency, and user satisfaction.', 'Melody L. Gabas ', '[\"Roxas, Zailyn\",\"Quintana, Errol John\",\"Isais, Wency\",\"Bravo, Mark Justine\",\"Sillon, Althea Mae\"]', 2, 23, '9', '\"Industry, Innovation and Infrastructure\"', '{\"0\":0.0021397420205175877,\"1\":0.0002834494807757437,\"2\":0.03456302732229233,\"3\":0.001286582089960575,\"4\":0.00009607191168470308,\"5\":0.00023005610273685306,\"6\":0.0003033024549949914,\"7\":0.07830244302749634,\"8\":0.8719746470451355,\"9\":0.0013937216717749834,\"10\":0.0004343055479694158,\"11\":0.0001409843098372221,\"12\":0.0001529109722469002,\"13\":0.000045